    <description>Laura Secorun is an independent journalist obsessed with borders and everything that crosses them. Born in Barcelona, based in Nairobi, she writes about development, migration and human trafficking in East Africa. Her work appears regularly in Newsweek, The Guardian, Slate, Fortune and others.
